place.name: SWARRATON
place.gazetteerText: SWARRATON, a parish in Alresford district, Hants; 3 miles NNW of Alresford r. station. Post town, Alresford. Acres, 743. Real property, £892. Pop., 100. Houses, 22. The Grange is the seat of Lord Ashburton. The living is a rectory, united with Northington, in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £110.* Patron, Lord Ashburton. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
